caption: Bar associations in small cities like Barcelona have far better museums and they're free. The content of the museum really doesn't justify the price.

Very interesting museum that I recently had the opportunity to visit in a group with a guide who was very passionate about the subject. The collections are renewed and temporary exhibitions are organized, including on the Dreyfus affair which was held at the museum from October 10 to December 31, 2019.

Truly a fabulous place, full of history and stories of all kinds. A great visit during the 2013 Heritage Days, with a wonderful "guide" who filled us with juicy anecdotes on the great trials in French history and on certain great characters.

Tiny museum! For 4 people: the price is 36 euros. They charge children 6 euros! The height! Just a cellar to visit. We thought there was a room upstairs to visit: everything was closed. VERY VERY VERY DISAPPOINTED.
It is not really a museum but rather an exhibition room with some pieces from certain trials. Interesting guided tour but a little too art-focused

An incredible place filled with the spirit of freedom. Definitely not the most popular attraction, but very spacious and beautiful. The architecture is as minimalistic as possible, but sophisticated. This is a place that I will gladly return to again.
The museum is small but well stocked. The visit was very documented and rich in emotions.
To be discovered during heritage days, you will leave with a smile (look at the 2013 review to better understand). You will find there the list of lawyers converted... to other functions.
Nice location but very small and therefore crazy price: 12€/person for a single room! It's not worth it.
Small, little-known museum but worth a visit.  History of majesty and various famous news items.
A passionate guide for an exhibition full of history on the First World War
Very interesting. I had the opportunity to visit with a very passionate guide. Very beautiful pieces, a rich collection.
Showcases displaying objects full of history, magnificent paintings and an exciting guided tour
I found the Dreyfus subject very interesting and the guide explained it to us well.
A single visiting room 12 euros. Excessive price
More discreet is hard, and expensive.... too bad
